theorem Topology.closure_inter_closure_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A B : Set X) :
    closure (A ∩ closure B) ⊆ closure A ∩ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : x ∈ closure A := by
    -- Since `A ∩ closure B ⊆ A`, taking closures yields the inclusion.
    have h_sub : (A ∩ closure B : Set X) ⊆ A := by
      intro y hy
      exact hy.1
    exact (closure_mono h_sub) hx
  have hxB : x ∈ closure B := by
    -- Similarly, `A ∩ closure B ⊆ closure B`.
    have h_sub : (A ∩ closure B : Set X) ⊆ closure B := by
      intro y hy
      exact hy.2
    exact (closure_mono h_sub) hx
  exact ⟨hxA, hxB⟩
